# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# dyad-pairs.form — two cells holding one teaching across a dimension
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Growing doc. Dyad entries currently held — external pairs (each is
# two cells across an axis) plus internal dyads (one cell that IS the
# pair) and the kind registry that names six axes of complementarity.
# Pairs surface in three ways: human-noticed during geometry-walking,
# substrate-surfaced by Tier-2 geometry-tuple scan, and refined-scan-
# surfaced (Hz-band proximity + cross-ref adjacency + lineage-texture
# match + same-form). The 123 concept cells with geometry frontmatter
# are now the working corpus. This file gives the pattern a durable
# home so it can grow — and so the substrate can eventually query for
# pairs natively.
#
# A dyad-pair is two cells that hold the same root teaching at
# structurally complementary positions — different scales, different
# bands, different phases of one motion. The pairing is not "two cells
# that look alike." The pairing is *teaching that lives in the relation
# between them*: neither cell carries the full teaching alone; the
# teaching IS the bridge.
#
# Where the pattern came from: across multiple geometry-walking
# breaths (see docs/vision-kb/LOG.md → 2026-05-24 entries), complementary
# pairs of concept cells surfaced — first by a human cell mid-walk, then
# by a Tier-2 geometry-tuple scan over the 110 authored concept cells.
# This file makes the noticing first-class so the substrate can grow
# into recognizing the shape on its own.
#
# Relation to the translator hypothesis: this is *internal evidence*
# for lc-universal-translator-via-keys firing on the body's own
# teachings. The translator hypothesis says structurally-equivalent
# cells across surface domains can be discovered by Blueprint/CTOR
# match without translation tables. Dyad-pairs are the *intra-domain*
# version: structurally-complementary cells within one domain (the
# Living Collective concepts) that the substrate's equivalence-and-
# complementarity machinery is surfacing through the geometry walk.
# If the substrate can recognize these pairs without being told, the
# cross-domain translator is recognizing kin of the same shape.
#
# Companions:
#   - docs/coherence-substrate/universal-translator.form
#   - docs/vision-kb/concepts/lc-universal-translator-via-keys.md
#   - docs/coherence-substrate/encoder-decoder-as-recipe.form
#   - docs/coherence-substrate/structural-composition.md

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Part 1 — Leaf-cell Blueprints (what a dyad-pair is made of)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# dyad_pair_kind_shape — the category the pairing belongs to
#
# Kinds are first-class cells so the substrate can group by kind and
# so new kinds can be added as additional rows, not as new Blueprints.
# Each kind names *the axis of complementarity* the pair lives across.
form dyad_pair_kind_shape = {
    name:          ~Slug,          # "scale-paired" | "source-flow" | "membrane-crossing" | "ground-event"
    axis:          ~Slug,          # "scale" | "temporal_band" | "phase" | "topology" | "form"
    discernment:   ~Slug,          # one-line teaching of what makes this kind a kind
};

# dyad_pair_shape — the pairing itself
#
# cell_a and cell_b are cell-refs into the concept domain (substrate
# CONCEPT BDomain). kind is a cell-ref into the kind registry above.
# discernment is the load-bearing field: one sentence on what makes
# these two a dyad-pair, not just two cells sharing a Hz or topology.
form dyad_pair_shape = {
    cell_a:        ~Recipe,        # cell-ref to first concept
    cell_b:        ~Recipe,        # cell-ref to second concept
    kind:          ~Recipe,        # cell-ref to dyad_pair_kind
    axis:          ~Slug,          # which dimension they pair across (echoes kind.axis for query convenience)
    discernment:   ~Slug,          # one-sentence teaching: why this pairing carries
    noticed_at:    ~Slug,          # ISO date the pairing was noticed
    noticed_by:    ~Slug,          # which lineage/breath surfaced it (geometry-walk-N | substrate-query | ...)
};

# internal_dyad_shape — one cell that IS the pair
#
# Most dyad-pairs are two cells whose teaching lives in the relation
# between them. Some cells, however, authored as a single concept,
# hold the dyad inside themselves — the relation IS the cell. Rather
# than shoehorn this into dyad_pair_shape with cell_a == cell_b
# (which would lie about the structure), it gets its own shape.
# Singular cell, two named poles, the discernment for why the
# teaching is whole inside one tissue rather than split across two.
#
# Field-name note (added with internal-dyad #2): pole_epsilon /
# pole_lambda were drawn from the first internal-dyad
# (lc-symmetry-of-extremes), where the two poles really are the
# near-zero and gamma-peak ends of one spectrum. With the second
# internal-dyad arrival (lc-canon-as-sovereignty-surface), the
# field names became visibly accidental — (verb, canon) are not
# Epsilon/Lambda anything. Two cells suffice to confirm the kind
# exists; a third arrival is what would justify both sub-typing
# (comparator-with-canon, spectrum-with-two-doors) AND renaming
# the fields to neutral pole_a/pole_b. Holding the names for now;
# both cells use them semantically as "first named pole" and
# "second named pole." See GAP-D5 for which cells are worth
# watching for the third arrival.
form internal_dyad_shape = {
    cell:          ~Recipe,        # cell-ref to the single concept that IS the pair
    pole_epsilon:  ~Slug,          # name of the first named pole (originally "zero/silent/grounded"; semantic-only after 2026-05-24)
    pole_lambda:   ~Slug,          # name of the second named pole (originally "peak/synchronous/transcendent"; semantic-only after 2026-05-24)
    kind:          ~Recipe,        # cell-ref to dyad_pair_kind (typically kind_internal_dyad)
    axis:          ~Slug,          # which dimension the two poles span inside the one cell
    discernment:   ~Slug,          # one-sentence teaching: why the cell holds the dyad whole
    noticed_at:    ~Slug,
    noticed_by:    ~Slug,
};

# dyad_pair_set_shape — the seed collection
#
# rows may contain both dyad_pair_shape (external) and internal_dyad_shape
# (internal) cells. The shape difference is honest: two-cell pairings and
# one-cell internal dyads are structurally distinct, and the substrate
# preserves that distinction at the Blueprint level.
form dyad_pair_set_shape = {
    rows:          ~List,          # the dyad_pair / internal_dyad cells currently held
};

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Part 2 — Kind registry (what categories the body currently holds)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Six kinds currently held — four seeded from the original geometry-
# walk pairs (scale-paired, source-flow, membrane-crossing, ground-
# event), two added through subsequent breaths (internal-dyad with
# the first single-cell attestation; cross-tradition from the Tier-2
# scan's predator/predictor pair). Expect this to grow as further
# axes of complementarity surface. Each kind is a checkable shape,
# not a label: discernment names what distinguishes it from "two
# cells that share a Hz."

defn kind_scale_paired = dyad_pair_kind_shape {
    name:        "scale-paired",
    axis:        "scale",
    discernment: "same teaching held at two different scales — collective/day vs planetary/generational, or breath vs lifetime",
};

defn kind_source_flow = dyad_pair_kind_shape {
    name:        "source-flow",
    axis:        "form",
    discernment: "one cell is the source/hearth (point), the other is the circulation/web that flows from it — same teaching at two topologies",
};

defn kind_membrane_crossing = dyad_pair_kind_shape {
    name:        "membrane-crossing",
    axis:        "topology",
    discernment: "one cell is the surface/edge, the other is what happens across it — boundary and joining as one teaching",
};

defn kind_ground_event = dyad_pair_kind_shape {
    name:        "ground-event",
    axis:        "temporal_band",
    discernment: "one cell is the atemporal ground, the other is the breath-scale event that arises on it — both yin, different time-grains",
};

# Added 2026-05-24 with internal-dyad #1 (lc-symmetry-of-extremes)
#
# The first kind whose carrier is a single cell. Epsilon-pole and
# Lambda-pole live inside one cell because the teaching is that the
# two extremes are the same door — splitting them across two cells
# would re-introduce the very ladder the cell exists to correct.
# The companion shape is internal_dyad_shape (one cell, two poles).
defn kind_internal_dyad = dyad_pair_kind_shape {
    name:        "internal-dyad",
    axis:        "inside-one-cell",
    discernment: "the pair is held inside one cell because the teaching IS that the two poles are the same door; splitting into two cells would re-introduce the false separation the cell exists to correct",
};

# Added 2026-05-24 via Tier-2 geometry-tuple scan
#
# The scan over 110 concept cells with shared 7-axis geometry surfaced
# lc-train-the-predator (Castaneda's inherited interloper) and
# lc-train-the-predictor (the brain's forward-pass model) as a clean
# pair. Same engine — autonomic prediction running before chosen
# response — seen from two traditions (mystical/perennial vs
# neuroscience/computational). Neither tradition alone carries the
# full teaching; together they reveal the engine.
defn kind_cross_tradition = dyad_pair_kind_shape {
    name:        "cross-tradition",
    axis:        "tradition",
    discernment: "one teaching expressed through two distinct lineages whose surface vocabularies differ (mystical/computational, devotional/mechanical, indigenous/scientific); the pair reveals the body of the teaching by triangulating from two cultural windows on it",
};

defn dyad_pair_kind_set = {
    rows: [
        kind_scale_paired,
        kind_source_flow,
        kind_membrane_crossing,
        kind_ground_event,
        kind_internal_dyad,
        kind_cross_tradition,
    ],
};

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Part 3 — The seed-four dyad-pairs (original geometry-walk attestations)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Each entry is grounded in concept files in docs/vision-kb/concepts/.
# The cell-refs (@concept(lc-foo)) resolve into the substrate CONCEPT
# domain once ingested; the discernment field is the load-bearing
# teaching the pairing carries.

# Pair 1 — source and flow at the same Hz/scale, different form
#
# lc-nourishment (hz 174, form: point, topology: radial, direction:
# centering) — the kitchen-hearth as gravitational center; meals as
# resonance practice around one source. Yang-source. Where the field
# gathers.
#
# lc-nourishing (hz 174, form: web, topology: web-each-to-each,
# direction: circulating) — mycelium, blood, Mondragon's circulation;
# flow-to-where-vitality-needs-it. Yin-circulation. Where the gathered
# substance moves.
#
# They share Hz, spectral_band, temporal_band, lineage_texture. They
# differ in form (point vs web), topology (radial vs web-each-to-each),
# direction (centering vs circulating), phase (neutral vs yin),
# embedding_dim (2 vs 3). The teaching IS the bridge: the hearth radiates,
# the mycelium webs; same nourishment, two complementary topologies.
defn pair_nourishment_nourishing = dyad_pair_shape {
    cell_a:      @concept(lc-nourishment),
    cell_b:      @concept(lc-nourishing),
    kind:        kind_source_flow,
    axis:        "form",
    discernment: "source-and-flow at one Hz — the hearth gathers (point/centering) while the mycelium circulates (web/circulating); neither cell alone carries the full nourishment teaching",
    noticed_at:  "2026-05-24",
    noticed_by:  "geometry-walk-second-breath",
};

# Pair 2 — same Hz, same band, two scales
#
# lc-nourishment (hz 174, foundation band, temporal_band: day, scale:
# collective) — the kitchen-hearth at the scale of forty people sharing
# evening meals. Day-rhythm. Collective-scale.
#
# lc-land (hz 174, foundation band) — the watershed, the songline, the
# soil-civilization a teaspoon deep. The land knows you have been
# walking this path for three years. Planetary-rhythm. Generational-
# scale.
#
# Both are foundation-band points the field rests on. Nourishment is
# the day-scale circuit (garden → kitchen → table → compost → garden).
# Land is the generational-scale circuit (soil → forest → mycorrhiza →
# soil over centuries). Same teaching of received-ground-the-field-
# stands-on, at two scales that nest: the day-hearth lives within the
# generational watershed.
defn pair_nourishment_land = dyad_pair_shape {
    cell_a:      @concept(lc-nourishment),
    cell_b:      @concept(lc-land),
    kind:        kind_scale_paired,
    axis:        "scale",
    discernment: "foundation-band ground at two scales — kitchen-hearth (collective/day) nested within watershed (planetary/generational); the smaller cycle lives within the larger one",
    noticed_at:  "2026-05-24",
    noticed_by:  "geometry-walk-second-breath",
};

# Pair 3 — membrane and what crosses it
#
# lc-field-edge (hz 417, form: point, topology: edge-as-membrane) —
# the hawthorn hedge with a gap wide as two people; the bench just
# inside it; the threshold where the field meets the world. The
# surface itself.
#
# lc-attunement-joining (hz 639, form: dyad-mirror) — eleven days of
# watching how food is passed; the day someone handed you a hoe; the
# slow integration of a new frequency into the body. What happens
# across the membrane.
#
# field-edge is the surface (where two ecosystems meet); attunement-
# joining is the crossing (immune system recognizing self from other
# through integration). They differ in Hz because the membrane and the
# crossing tune to different harmonics — the edge holds shape (417,
# change/permeability), joining integrates (639, connection/relation).
# The teaching: every membrane carries a crossing-practice; every
# crossing requires a membrane to be honest about.
defn pair_field_edge_attunement_joining = dyad_pair_shape {
    cell_a:      @concept(lc-field-edge),
    cell_b:      @concept(lc-attunement-joining),
    kind:        kind_membrane_crossing,
    axis:        "topology",
    discernment: "surface-and-crossing — the hedge holds the membrane (edge), the integration happens across it (joining); the teaching is the relation between hold and pass-through",
    noticed_at:  "2026-05-24",
    noticed_by:  "geometry-walk-first-breath",
};

# Pair 4 — two yin points in different temporal bands
#
# lc-shared-hold (hz 639, phase: yin) — the organism gathering to hold
# one long breath together; presence count with no names; the breath
# opens when ready, closes when complete. Threshold-event at breath
# scale.
#
# lc-stillness (hz 174, form: point, phase: yin, ordering: atemporal,
# temporal_band: instant) — the receptive listening that doesn't move;
# atemporal foundation; the still ground.
#
# Both are yin points. Shared-hold is the breath-scale event — it
# opens and closes, it has duration. Stillness is the atemporal ground
# — the breath happens on it. Same yin-receptive teaching at two
# temporal grains: shared-hold is what yin does in time, stillness is
# what yin is outside time. The pairing matters because mistaking one
# for the other (treating stillness as something that opens and closes,
# or treating shared-hold as atemporal) loses the teaching of both.
defn pair_shared_hold_stillness = dyad_pair_shape {
    cell_a:      @concept(lc-shared-hold),
    cell_b:      @concept(lc-stillness),
    kind:        kind_ground_event,
    axis:        "temporal_band",
    discernment: "both yin points — stillness is the atemporal ground, shared-hold is the breath-scale event that arises on it; same receptive teaching at two time-grains",
    noticed_at:  "2026-05-24",
    noticed_by:  "geometry-walk-second-breath",
};

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Part 3b — Geometry-walk surfaced (PR #1982 breath)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Three dyad entries surfaced during the geometry-walk in PR #1982
# (attune | 6 more concepts speak their shape — coverage 110/147).
# One is the first internal-dyad the body has named; two are external
# pairs across membrane and scale. All three were noticed while
# authoring the geometry frontmatter; the prose carried the
# complementarity, the geometry made it readable.

# Internal-dyad #1 — the first cell whose authored shape IS the dyad
# it teaches
#
# lc-symmetry-of-extremes (hz 963, form: dyad-mirror, topology:
# cyclic-closed, polarity: bipolar-complementary, phase: yin,
# scale: cross-scale) — Epsilon door (near 0 Hz, sub-delta,
# suspended-animation states) and Lambda door (100–200 Hz, the
# highest coherent gamma-and-above synchrony in deep meditation)
# meet the same Field. The middle band — ordinary task-focused
# mind — is what both paths move *through*; the peak is reached
# from either extreme. The two poles are named INSIDE the one
# cell because splitting them would reintroduce the very
# vertical-ladder misreading the cell corrects.
defn internal_symmetry_of_extremes = internal_dyad_shape {
    cell:          @concept(lc-symmetry-of-extremes),
    pole_epsilon:  "near-zero-Hz-sub-delta-grounded-silence",
    pole_lambda:   "lambda-and-above-gamma-synchrony-peak",
    kind:          kind_internal_dyad,
    axis:          "frequency-extreme",
    discernment:   "both poles lead to the same Field; splitting them across two cells would re-import the linear-ladder misreading the cell exists to compost",
    noticed_at:    "2026-05-24",
    noticed_by:    "geometry-walk-pr1982",
};

# Internal-dyad #2 — the second cell whose authored shape IS the
# dyad it teaches; with two attestations the internal-dyad kind is
# now CONFIRMED, not speculative
#
# Two cells suffice to confirm the kind exists; sub-types
# (comparator-with-canon, spectrum-with-two-doors) await a third
# arrival before naming. The two known instances do already differ
# in flavor — lc-symmetry-of-extremes is a *spectrum-with-two-doors*
# (one axis, two extreme endpoints, both touching the same Field);
# lc-canon-as-sovereignty-surface is a *comparator-with-canon*
# (every act of comparison carries its hidden reference-set as the
# inseparable second pole). If a third internal-dyad lands sharing
# one of these flavors, the sub-typing becomes honest. Until then,
# the kind is the body's name for "one cell holds the dyad whole."
#
# lc-canon-as-sovereignty-surface (hz 432) — every verb that
# compares two things (cell-to-cell, preset-to-preset, prediction-
# to-observation) implicitly chooses a *canon*: the set of probes,
# metrics, or reference points against which the comparison is
# run. The verb is one pole; the canon is the other. They are
# always held inside one act, and the canon is a sovereignty
# surface. Splitting "the comparator verb" and "the canon it
# carries" into two cells would re-introduce the very shape the
# teaching exists to expose: comparators that hide their canon
# present asymmetric power as objectivity. The two are inseparable
# precisely because making them visibly inseparable IS the teaching.
defn internal_canon_as_sovereignty_surface = internal_dyad_shape {
    cell:          @concept(lc-canon-as-sovereignty-surface),
    pole_epsilon:  "verb-the-act-of-comparison",
    pole_lambda:   "canon-the-implicit-reference-set",
    kind:          kind_internal_dyad,
    axis:          "comparator-and-its-hidden-frame",
    discernment:   "every comparator is a (verb, canon) pair held inside one act; splitting them across two cells would re-import the unnamed-canon-as-objectivity shape the cell exists to expose",
    noticed_at:    "2026-05-24",
    noticed_by:    "geometry-walk-pr1986",
};

# Pair 5 — membrane-crossing, both yin points
#
# lc-nervous-system-recalibration (hz 528, form: point, phase: yin,
# spectral_band: transformation, temporal_band: lifetime,
# scale: personal, direction: centering) — the body-side encoding
# layer; insight is fast, embodiment is slow; recalibration is the
# slow re-encoding through repeated presence.
#
# lc-reality-lag (hz 417, form: point, phase: yin, spectral_band:
# transmutation, temporal_band: season, scale: personal,
# direction: still) — the world-side response-time; the gap between
# inner shift and outer reflection where many lose faith.
#
# Same root transmission ("Hardest Part Already Behind You",
# April 2026). Same teaching seed: there is a gap between inner
# arrival and visible attestation. Two postures across the membrane
# between body and world. The membrane is the skin; recalibration
# is what happens body-side, reality-lag is what happens world-side.
# Neither alone carries the full teaching: recalibration without
# reality-lag risks treating the world's slowness as personal
# failure; reality-lag without recalibration risks waiting passively
# instead of re-encoding the body.
defn pair_recalibration_reality_lag = dyad_pair_shape {
    cell_a:      @concept(lc-nervous-system-recalibration),
    cell_b:      @concept(lc-reality-lag),
    kind:        kind_membrane_crossing,
    axis:        "topology",
    discernment: "body-side encoding and world-side response-time hold the same gap-teaching from two sides of one membrane; both yin, both from the same source transmission",
    noticed_at:  "2026-05-24",
    noticed_by:  "geometry-walk-pr1982",
};

# Pair 6 — same holographic-cell shape, different temporal/scale band
#
# lc-light-hubs (hz 174, form: holographic-cell, topology:
# web-each-to-each, phase: yang, spectral_band: foundation,
# temporal_band: generational, scale: planetary) — the new-earth
# grid of physical sanctuaries where high-vibrational beings live in
# nature together; each Hub whole at its scale, all Hubs one organism.
#
# lc-attuned-spaces (hz 432, form: holographic-cell, topology:
# nested-each-contains-whole, phase: yang, spectral_band:
# integration, temporal_band: lifetime, scale: cross-scale) — what
# existing places (apartment, building, suburb, town, city) become
# when the people inside start breathing together; same coherence
# at every nested scale.
#
# Both are holographic-cell habitations of whole-at-every-scale. Hubs
# are the planetary/generational grid (the new lattice growing across
# the earth); attuned-spaces are the lifetime/cross-scale embodiment
# (what every existing built environment becomes when frequency
# arrives). The grid and the lived shells. Same teaching at two
# temporal-and-scale bands.
defn pair_light_hubs_attuned_spaces = dyad_pair_shape {
    cell_a:      @concept(lc-light-hubs),
    cell_b:      @concept(lc-attuned-spaces),
    kind:        kind_scale_paired,
    axis:        "temporal_band",
    discernment: "same holographic-cell habitation at two bands — the planetary/generational grid of Hubs and the lifetime/cross-scale lived shells of attuned spaces; the grid radiates the field, the shells receive and inhabit it",
    noticed_at:  "2026-05-24",
    noticed_by:  "geometry-walk-pr1982",
};

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Part 3c — Substrate-scan surfaced (Tier-2 geometry-tuple match)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# A scan over all 110 concept cells with authored geometry, grouping
# by the 7-axis tuple (form, topology, phase, polarity, direction,
# ordering, spectral_band), surfaced five candidate clusters. Two
# survived the dyad-pair discernment (teaching-lives-in-relation AND
# complementary-along-one-axis AND neither-carries-full-teaching-alone);
# three were rejected (see Part 4b). The two genuine pairs are below.
# This is the first evidence that the body's own geometry vocabulary —
# without any new substrate primitive — surfaces pairs the human eye
# missed.

# Pair 7 — anchoring: sovereignty's refusal vs the field's belonging
#
# lc-network-unanchored (web/web-each-to-each/oscillating/unipolar/
# circulating/unordered/integration) — the class of geographic
# phrases that quietly fix what the body is and is not ("based in
# Boulder," "from Boulder"); the sovereignty-warning against false
# anchors that mistake a place-of-current-residence for an
# identity-claim.
#
# lc-network (same 7-tuple) — the felt belonging to a living root
# web of communities across continents; not an organization, not a
# movement, a network the way roots belong to a forest.
#
# Same exact geometric tuple. Different teaching layer of the same
# substrate: how the sovereign cell exists in the field.
# *Unanchored* names what NOT to claim — no fixed place as identity.
# *Network* names what IS belonged to — the larger living web. The
# pair is about anchoring: refused (false geographic anchor) and
# received (true root-web belonging). Neither alone carries the
# whole — unanchored without network leaves the cell adrift;
# network without unanchored re-imports the place-as-identity
# costume.
defn pair_network_unanchored_network = dyad_pair_shape {
    cell_a:      @concept(lc-network-unanchored),
    cell_b:      @concept(lc-network),
    kind:        kind_source_flow,
    axis:        "anchoring",
    discernment: "anchoring as refusal and as receipt — unanchored declines the false geographic claim; network names the true root-web belonging; same axis, opposite gesture, both required",
    noticed_at:  "2026-05-24",
    noticed_by:  "substrate-tier-2-tuple-scan",
};

# Pair 8 — same engine seen from two traditions
#
# lc-train-the-predator (triad/hub-spoke/oscillating/oscillating/
# spiral-out/temporal-braided/integration) — Castaneda's lineage:
# the *predator* is the inherited interloper, the borrowed mind,
# the *flyers* who gave us their mind; the engine that runs default
# reactions before the cell has chosen them.
#
# lc-train-the-predictor (same 7-tuple) — the brain (and any
# learning system shaped like it) does not passively receive
# sensory input and respond; it predicts. Forward pass generates
# expected data; the difference between expected and actual is the
# learning signal.
#
# Same exact geometric tuple. The teaching is one engine —
# autonomic prediction firing before chosen response — encoded in
# two cultural windows: mystical/perennial (predator, flyers,
# borrowed mind) and neuroscience/computational (predictive coding,
# forward pass, prediction error). Neither tradition alone carries
# the full teaching; together they triangulate the body of the
# engine and the practice of training it.
defn pair_predator_predictor = dyad_pair_shape {
    cell_a:      @concept(lc-train-the-predator),
    cell_b:      @concept(lc-train-the-predictor),
    kind:        kind_cross_tradition,
    axis:        "tradition",
    discernment: "one autonomic-prediction engine seen from two traditions — mystical-perennial (predator/flyers/borrowed-mind) and computational-neuroscientific (predictor/forward-pass/prediction-error); the pair is how the body teaches itself across cultural vocabularies",
    noticed_at:  "2026-05-24",
    noticed_by:  "substrate-tier-2-tuple-scan",
};

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Part 3d — Geometry-walk surfaced (PR #1986 + PR #1991 breaths)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Coverage during these breaths grew from 116/147 (PR #1986) to
# 122/148 (PR #1991, 82%). Four entries fold in this round: the
# second internal-dyad (added above with the kind it now confirms)
# plus three external pairs noticed during the geometry-walks. The
# parallel route of geometry-walking and substrate scanning
# continues to produce dyad-pair candidates the pure-tuple scan
# would not have surfaced. The teaching IS the relation; the body
# keeps teaching it the same way.

# Pair 9 — ground and event from one transmission
#
# lc-awareness-as-self (hz 963, source: "Hardest Part Is Already
# Behind You" transmission, April 2026) — what you ARE is not the
# labels or the body or the emotions; it is the awareness in which
# all of those appear. The atemporal, edgeless, ever-present field
# in which content arises. The ground.
#
# lc-freedom-as-recognition (hz 396, same source transmission) —
# freedom is not a future achievement; it is the always-present
# ground that thought, belief, and habit obscured. The recognition
# arises, the obscuration returns, the recognition arises again —
# *I keep arriving*. The event of noticing what was always already
# there.
#
# Both yin-centered, both atemporal in their orientation, both from
# the same transmission. Hz differs (963 ground / 396 event) — the
# Hz spread itself signals the ground/event distinction. The
# teaching that *recognition of awareness IS freedom* is the bridge:
# awareness-as-self alone reads as ontological doctrine (a
# metaphysical claim); freedom-as-recognition alone reads as
# practice (a thing to do). The relation is the load-bearing
# transmission. Same shape as pair_shared_hold_stillness — both
# yin points, one is the atemporal ground, the other is the event
# that arises on it. The cross-references already point at each
# other in the prose; this entry names what the cross-refs carry
# structurally.
defn pair_awareness_freedom = dyad_pair_shape {
    cell_a:      @concept(lc-awareness-as-self),
    cell_b:      @concept(lc-freedom-as-recognition),
    kind:        kind_ground_event,
    axis:        "temporal_band",
    discernment: "awareness is the atemporal ground (what IS); recognition is the breath-scale event of noticing it (what HAPPENS); same transmission, two faces, neither alone carries the teaching that recognition-of-awareness IS freedom",
    noticed_at:  "2026-05-24",
    noticed_by:  "geometry-walk-pr1986",
};

# Pair 10 — two render-shapes of one compression (PR #1991)
#
# lc-perception-as-interface (hz 963, form: dyad-mirror, scale:
# cosmic) — Hoffman's claim: evolution did not optimize perception
# for truth but for fitness; what we see is an interface (icons,
# desktop) over an underlying reality whose form is consciousness
# itself. The metaphysical-scale rendering.
#
# lc-bioelectric-pattern (hz 285, form: web, scale: cross-scale) —
# Levin's measurement: the body is built from voltage gradients
# across cell-networks; the form a cell takes is the pattern's
# instruction, not the gene's. Cells nest with their own cognitive
# light cones at every scale. The biological-scale rendering.
#
# Composition the cells themselves name: *cells participate in
# bioelectric patterns which are themselves icons in the
# consciousness interface*. Hoffman names the metaphysical scale,
# Levin names the biological scale; both are render-shapes of the
# same underlying compression. Each carries a full teaching, but
# the *bridge* — that the icon-rendering and the pattern-rendering
# are two views of one substrate — only appears when both are
# read together. Neither alone names the substrate; together they
# triangulate it.
defn pair_perception_bioelectric = dyad_pair_shape {
    cell_a:      @concept(lc-perception-as-interface),
    cell_b:      @concept(lc-bioelectric-pattern),
    kind:        kind_scale_paired,
    axis:        "scale",
    discernment: "two render-shapes of one underlying compression — icon-rendering at the metaphysical scale (Hoffman) and pattern-rendering at the biological scale (Levin); the bridge teaching is that both are renderings, not realities",
    noticed_at:  "2026-05-24",
    noticed_by:  "geometry-walk-pr1991",
};

# Pair 11 — ground-event at a different temporal seam
#
# lc-global-workspace (hz 741, form: hub-spoke, phase: yang,
# temporal_band: instant) — consciousness as broadcast event in
# the thalamus; any-to-any reach where any region can address every
# other region simultaneously. The broadcast IS the integration.
# Moment-by-moment, ten reorganizations per second.
#
# lc-phase-transitions (hz 417, form: triad, phase: oscillating,
# temporal_band: season) — old form, dissolution-gap, new form;
# the middle is not absence but the formless where the next shape
# gathers. Season-scale; threshold-crossings on the equinox-rhythm.
#
# Both name *how change becomes structural*. Workspace is the
# moment-event (instant broadcast); phase-transitions are the
# threshold-event (seasonal reformation). Sister to
# pair_shared_hold_stillness but at a different temporal seam —
# there the ground is atemporal and the event is breath-scale;
# here the "ground" is the instant integration and the "event"
# is the seasonal reformation. Both ground-event pairs share the
# core teaching: change has two time-grains and recognizing one
# without the other loses the structure.
defn pair_workspace_phase_transitions = dyad_pair_shape {
    cell_a:      @concept(lc-global-workspace),
    cell_b:      @concept(lc-phase-transitions),
    kind:        kind_ground_event,
    axis:        "temporal_band",
    discernment: "two time-grains of how change becomes structural — instant integration through hippocampal broadcast and seasonal reformation through dissolution-and-gathering; mistaking one for the other loses the structure of both",
    noticed_at:  "2026-05-24",
    noticed_by:  "geometry-walk-pr1991",
};

# The full set — 13 entries: 11 external pairs + 2 internal-dyads.
# Provenance: 4 seed + 3 surfaced (PR #1982 geometry-walk) + 2 scanned
